{"questionId":"9083501","questionHtml":"<p>A mass is released from the top of a smooth ramp of height <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math></em>. After leaving the ramp, the&nbsp;mass slides on a rough horizontal surface.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/1be6da6c88a3258b83bbad41025856fca6b63e99.png\"></p>\n<p>The mass comes to rest in a distance <em>d</em>. What is the coefficient of dynamic friction between&nbsp;the mass and the horizontal surface?</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;</mtext><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><mi>h</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;</mtext><msqrt><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;</mtext><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mi>h</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;</mtext><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>d</mi></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9083501","referenceCode":"21M.1A.SL.TZ1.5","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A mass is released from the top of a smooth ramp of height h. After leaving the ramp, the mass slides on a rough horizontal surface. The mass comes to rest in a distance d. What is","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"5","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","A.2 Forces and momentum","A. Space, time and motion","A.3 Work, energy and power"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}